list.name: Changes
list.comment: Stage 8: More Pawn work, dealt with the weird 2 tile move that pawns can do as a first move, so added a way to check if it was a piece's first move (WIP). Added a check to see if a piece was white or black that I can actually call. Added row exclusions to BoardUtils(WIP). Adding a lot of stubbed out garbage but will fix it later, stubs make it easier to write it out

task.summary: Stage 2: still the tile class. added as much immutability as I could for the purposes of learning. it makes sense as well since chess is a very strict game. imported google's Guava libary to use ImmutableMap. Also got 99 fishing in OSRS earlier today! :)

Stage 2: still the tile class. added as much immutability as I could for the purposes of learning. it makes sense as well since chess is a very strict game. imported google's Guava libary to use ImmutableMap. Also got 99 fishing in OSRS earlier today! :)

Stage 3: Changes to Pieces, started working on the Knight. Added Alliance (color) as an enum since they're just a constant. Added getters for Alliance, pieces at certain tiles, and the tiles themselves

Stage 4: Fleshed out the Knight class, that should be mostly done for now. Added exclusion for certain columns due to the way I am calculating legal moves, will be adding more of those types of things to the BoardUtils class. Also changed the "list" of moves from an actual List to a Collection, as it makes more sense for Chess. Moved some declarations around as well. I think it is using more memory this way, but it's cleaner code so it works for me.

Stage 5: Did some housekeeping on the BoardUtils class, added a very convenient method that allows us to initialize and keep track of a particular column on the chess board. Added said method into the Knight class in the column exclusions. More work on the Knight class in general, but now the ability to capture the information about moves is laid out (attacking Moves vs Major Piece moves atm), or at least some sort of a barebones framework. More Board class work to come.

Stage 6: The Queen has arrived. Pretty simple honestly, a very quick copy and paste from Rook and Bishop and good to go. Next should be the Pawn, not quite sure how I'm handling that one but I guess we will see. Job search still killing me. Also my HC Ironman died yesterday. rank 896 global.

Stage 7: basic Pawn added, had to add some things to the Alliance class since pawns move in opposite directions. Stubbed out some code for the moves, will add a special "pawnMove" next time I work on this.

Stage 8: More Pawn work, dealt with the weird 2 tile move that pawns can do as a first move, so added a way to check if it was a piece's first move (WIP). Added a check to see if a piece was white or black that I can actually call. Added row exclusions to BoardUtils(WIP). Adding a lot of stubbed out garbage but will fix it later, stubs make it easier to write it out
